==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eu
<hw>Eu</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <grk>e'y^</grk> well, orig.
neut. of <grk>e'y`s</grk> good; prob. connected with Skr. <ets>su</ets>,
from the same root as E. <ets>is</ets>; or with Skr. <ets>vasu</ets>
good, prob. fr. the same root as E. <ets>was</ets>.]</ety> <def>A prefix
used frequently in composition, signifying <xex>well</xex>,
<xex>good</xex>, <xex>advantageous</xex>; -- the opposite of
<xex>dys-</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

